Spanish giants FC Barcelona have, on Thursday, confirmed the latest altogether untimely blow to the club’s personnel ranks. The latest member of Xavi Hernandez’s squad to have picked up an injury? Clement Lenglet. Taking to the club’s social media platforms this afternoon, the Blaugrana announced that stopper Lenglet has picked up a problem in the ‘femoral biceps in his left hamstring’, ahead of an upcoming spell on the sidelines. Rangnick Explains Lingard Stay Linked To Greenwood Adebomehin Appointed As Substantive SGoF Ensuing word stemming from the Spanish media, meanwhile, points towards a likely lengthy absence for the Frenchman, amid suggestions that Lenglet could be unavailable for selection for as long as five weeks. The former Sevilla man joins fellow central defenders Eric Garcia and Samuel Umtiti on the treatment table in the Catalan capital, amid what is fast developing into a full-blown crisis at the heart of Xavi’s backline. It is safe to say that the alarming situation in Barca’s backline could not have arrived at a much more inopportune moment for the faltering heavyweights. This comes with the Blaugrana set to return to action this weekend, in a crunch La Liga showdown with champions Atletico Madrid. POLL The matchup marks a crucial one amid the battle for a top-4 berth in the Spanish top-flight, with Diego Simeone’s troops currently occupying the final Champions League qualification berth. Barca, though, sit just a point adrift of the Rojiblancos in 5th, meaning a victory at the Camp Nou in 72 hours’ time could go a long way towards guiding Xavi and co. back towards the top tier of European club football.